---
import ArticleLayout from '../../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
import Terminal from '../../../components/Terminal.astro';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Why port 3000 stays free &mdash; Git Treeline"
  description="OAuth, Stripe, Mapbox, and CORS all break when your port changes. Treeline's proxy keeps localhost:3000 as a stable facade across every worktree."
  canonical="https://git-treeline.dev/use-cases/integrations-urls/"
  breadcrumb="Use cases"
  breadcrumbHref="/use-cases/"
  heading="Why port 3000 stays&nbsp;free"
  lead='OAuth providers, Stripe webhooks, Mapbox API keys, and CORS allowlists are all registered to <code class="text-white">localhost:3000</code>. That works when you have one copy of the app. It breaks the moment you run two.'
>
  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-10">The problem</h2>
  <p class="text-muted mb-4">
    Git worktrees let you work on multiple branches at the same time, each in its own directory. But each copy of the app needs its own port &mdash; branch A on 3000, branch B on 3010, branch C on 3020. The moment branch B starts on port 3010:
  </p>
  <ul class="text-muted space-y-2 list-disc pl-5 mb-6">
    <li><strong class="text-white">OAuth</strong> redirects are configured for <code class="text-accent-light">localhost:3000/auth/callback</code> &mdash; the provider rejects the redirect from <code class="text-white">:3010</code></li>
    <li><strong class="text-white">Mapbox / Google Maps</strong> validate the page origin &mdash; tile requests from <code class="text-white">localhost:3010</code> are denied</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white">Stripe webhooks</strong> point at <code class="text-accent-light">localhost:3000/webhooks</code> &mdash; events never reach the branch B server</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white">CORS policies</strong> allowlist <code class="text-accent-light">localhost:3000</code> &mdash; API calls from <code class="text-white">:3010</code> are blocked</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-muted mb-8">
    You&rsquo;re forced to choose: run on the &ldquo;right&rdquo; port and stop all other branches, or reconfigure every third-party dashboard for every branch. Neither scales.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-14">The design decision</h2>
  <p class="text-muted mb-4">
    Treeline deliberately never allocates port 3000 &mdash; or any common framework default (4000, 5000, 8000, 8080). Worktree servers bind to ports in a managed range that the developer never needs to type. Port 3000 stays empty so the proxy can claim it.
  </p>
  <p class="text-muted mb-8">
    <code class="text-accent-light">gtl proxy 3000</code> sits on the port that third-party services expect and routes traffic to whichever worktree you&rsquo;re working on. The external world always sees <code class="text-white">localhost:3000</code>. You rotate what&rsquo;s behind it.
  </p>

  <div class="mb-8">
    <Terminal>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <p><span class="text-accent-light">$</span> <span class="text-white">gtl proxy 3000</span></p>
        <p class="text-muted">Proxying <span class="text-accent">:3000</span> &rarr; <span class="text-accent">:4010</span> <span class="text-muted">(feature-auth)</span></p>
        <p class="text-muted text-base mt-3"># OAuth callback &rarr; :4010 &#10003;</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-base"># Stripe webhook &rarr; :4010 &#10003;</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-base"># Mapbox origin  &rarr; :4010 &#10003;</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-base"># CORS passes    &rarr; :4010 &#10003;</p>
      </div>
    </Terminal>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-14">Two layers, one config</h2>
  <p class="text-muted mb-4">
    The proxy handles what&rsquo;s external. Branch-named URLs handle what&rsquo;s local. Both run simultaneously:
  </p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-surface-border mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-surface-border bg-surface">
          <th class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-accent-light">Audience</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-accent-light">URL</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-accent-light">How</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-surface-border text-muted">
        <tr>
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Your browser</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-white"><code class="text-accent-light">myapp-feature.prt.dev</code></td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="text-accent-light">gtl serve</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="px-4 py-3">OAuth / Stripe / Maps / CORS</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-white"><code class="text-accent-light">localhost:3000</code></td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="text-accent-light">gtl proxy</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Public internet (webhooks, CI)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-white"><code class="text-accent-light">myapp-feature.example.dev</code></td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="text-accent-light">gtl tunnel</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="px-4 py-3">A colleague or client</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-white">Disposable token-gated URL</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3"><code class="text-accent-light">gtl share</code></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-14">What the developer sees</h2>
  <div class="mb-8">
    <Terminal>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <p class="text-muted text-base"># Create a worktree &mdash; treeline allocates port 4010</p>
        <p><span class="text-accent-light">$</span> <span class="text-white">gtl new feature/oauth-refactor</span></p>
        <p class="text-muted">Allocated port <span class="text-accent">4010</span>, cloned database, wrote .env</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted text-base"># Start the server &mdash; runs on 4010, not 3000</p>
        <p><span class="text-accent-light">$</span> <span class="text-white">gtl start</span></p>
        <p class="text-muted text-accent">==&gt; https://myapp-feature-oauth-refactor.prt.dev</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted text-base"># Route port 3000 to this worktree</p>
        <p><span class="text-accent-light">$</span> <span class="text-white">gtl proxy 3000</span></p>
        <p class="text-muted">Proxying <span class="text-accent">:3000</span> &rarr; <span class="text-accent">:4010</span></p>
      </div>
    </Terminal>
  </div>
  <p class="text-muted mb-8">
    No port numbers in the browser. No OAuth reconfiguration. No Stripe dashboard changes. The developer works on any branch, and the external world sees the same origin it always has.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-14">Read next</h2>
  <ul class="text-muted space-y-3 list-disc pl-5 mb-8">
    <li><a href="/features/networking/" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">Networking feature page</a> &mdash; deep dive on all four commands: <code class="text-accent-light">serve</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">proxy</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">tunnel</code>, and <code class="text-accent-light">share</code></li>
    <li><a href="/docs/#networking" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">Docs: networking</a> &mdash; config options, port forwarding rules, and Safari workarounds</li>
    <li><a href="/use-cases/multi-repo/" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">Multi-repo</a> &mdash; when the problem is cross-project service resolution, not external URLs</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="text-center">
    <a href="/use-cases/" class="text-sm text-accent-light hover:text-accent">All use cases</a>
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
